Putin called on the Ukrainian military to immediately lay down their arms
24 February 2022, 05:56
Photo: ©
RIA Novosti / Alexey Nikolsky
Read ren.tv in
Russian President Vladimir Putin called on the Ukrainian military to immediately lay down their arms.
He pointed out that our fathers, grandfathers and great-grandfathers did not defend our Motherland so that today neo-Nazis would seize power in Ukraine and give allegiance to an “anti-people junta that robs and mocks” the people.
“Do not follow her attack orders. I urge you to immediately lay down your arms and go home. All members of the Ukrainian army who comply with this requirement will be able to freely leave the combat zone and return to their families,” -
