Ukrainian Su-27 fighter "escaped" to Romania
24 February 2022, 11:12
Read ren.tv in
A Ukrainian Su-27 military aircraft was spotted in Romanian airspace on the morning of February 24. Accompanied by two Romanian fighters, the plane landed at the air base in Bacau. This was reported by the Romanian Ministry of Defense.
The reasons for the incident and the motives of the Ukrainian fighter pilot have not been specified.
It is reported that the Su-27 made an unauthorized flight in northern Romania. At around 06:15 (07:15 Moscow time), two F-16 Fighting Falcon aircraft of the Romanian Air Force were scrambled to clarify the situation. The plane, belonging to the Ukrainian Air Force, was escorted to the air base in Bacau, where it immediately landed.
“After landing, the Ukrainian military pilot placed himself at the disposal of the Romanian authorities; the necessary legal measures in such situations will be taken.”
, the message says.
Aggravation of the situation in Donbass
On February 17, the Donetsk and Lugansk People's Republics announced the aggravation of the situation. The republics announced the evacuation of civilians.
On February 21, the leaders of the Donbass republics turned to Russian leader Vladimir Putin with a request to recognize the independence of the DPR and LPR. The head of state held a meeting of the Security Council, after which
signed two decrees
on the recognition of republics.
Treaties of friendship and cooperation were also signed with the independent Donetsk and Lugansk people's republics. State Duma and Federation Council
ratified
agreement data.
VTsIOM conducted a study, the data of which showed that 73% of Russians surveyed support the decision to recognize the independence of the DPR and LPR.
February 23, heads of the DPR and LPR
contacted
to Russian President Vladimir Putin with a request to help repel the aggression of Ukraine to prevent a humanitarian catastrophe and civilian casualties.
February 24, Russian leader
made a decision
about the special operation in Donbass.
