Putin: business in Russia should be provided with greater freedom
24 February 2022, 19:53
Photo: ©
RIA Novosti/Sergey Guneev
Read ren.tv in
Russian President Vladimir Putin said that business in our country should be provided with greater freedom. He said this during a meeting with representatives of Russian business circles.
The head of state appealed to business to work with the government in search of tools to support production, the economy and jobs.
“On the part of the government, the authorities in the broadest sense of the word, of course, I see the task as providing you with good conditions, providing more freedom.”
, said the Russian President.
Also during the meeting, Putin called a special operation in Donbass
forced measure
. He noted that Russia was left with no other chances.
Let us recall that in connection with the aggravated situation in the Donbass in recent days, Russia made a decision to recognize the independence of the Donetsk and Lugansk People's Republics. On February 23, the heads of the DPR and LPR appealed to the leadership of the Russian Federation with a request to help them counter Ukrainian aggression.
On the morning of February 24, Vladimir Putin announced the start of a special operation to protect Donbass, caused by circumstances requiring an immediate response.
